    "content": "<p>3\ufe0f\u20e3 Here&#39;s the 3rd post highlighting key new features of the upcoming v258 release of systemd. <a href=\"https://mastodon.social/tags/systemd258\" class=\"mention hashtag\" rel=\"tag\">#<span>systemd258</span></a></p><p>systemd-resolved  is a local DNS cache, widely deployed on Linux systems. What makes it different from older solutions is that it manages DNS settings primarily as a per network interface setting, instead of a per system setting. This reflects today&#39;s world better where systems tend to be connected to multiple networks at different times (or continously), instead of\u2026</p>",
