      "content": "<p>company networks/VPNs often serve their own non-public zones, and thus there is not just &quot;the one DNS&quot;, but many, and if in doubt we might need to ask multiple sources at the same time, and take what we can get.</p><p>With systemd v258 the query routing logic in systemd-resolved got substantially upgraded: in addition to routing queries to the DNS config of each interface (and optionaly one additional global one), there&#39;s now the ability to define arbitrary numbers of additional &quot;delegate zones&quot;:</p>",
