      "edited_at": null,
      "content": "<p>These are basically just combinations of DNS servers along with the domains to match queries with that shall be routed there.</p><p>For now this configuration is static (i.e. based on config files), but we hope to open this up to IPC too, i.e. that additional delegate zones can be added and removed any time.</p><p>In a way, delegate zones are like adding additional &quot;dummy&quot; network interfaces to the system that come with their own DNS config, but without any real connectivity.</p>",
