      "quotes_count": 0,
      "edited_at": null,
      "content": "<p><span class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"><a href=\"https://mastodon.social/@pid_eins\" class=\"u-url mention\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">@<span>pid_eins</span></a></span> are you aware DNS settings have been made part of PvDs 10 years ago? RFC7556. The ultimate takeaway (after you follow down the rathole and discard overly complex/dead approaches) is that distinct IPv6 LL addresses advertising distinct prefixes in RA/PIOs need to be treated as distinct networks on the same interface.</p><p>Either way, you need multiple distinct sets per interface.</p><p>(Good that we're catching up from 20 years ago to 10 years ago, but can we get to now? \ud83d\ude05)</p>",
