      "content": "<p><span class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"><a href=\"https://mastodon.social/@pid_eins\" class=\"u-url mention\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">@<span>pid_eins</span></a></span> (for more detail:) you need to read \u224810 more RFCs, some drafts, and follow IETF mailing lists to get to \"implicit PvDs by router's IPv6 LL address\" part, but \u2014 the real 'problem' here is that this is /actually needed/. The IETF is moving with its usual speed of molasses at this, but IPv6 multihoming needs to be solved, and this is the only viable way.</p><p>But if this systemd code is hard tied to interfaces conceptually\u2026 yeah, sorry, you'll need another refactor.</p>",
